@node 6 "Installing the game"

   No such thing here, just simply drag the directory over to disk
   or hard-drive and double click on the monty icon, the game SHOULD
   load and run.

   ANY PROBLEMS YOU MAY HAVE, PLEASE GET IN CONTACT WITH ME.


@endnode
@node 7 "Game options"

    From the title screen, selecting options, the following options
    will be displayed:
    
                            LIVES: 3
                            GAME MODE: NORMAL
                            HISCORE: LOAD
                            LEVEL CODE: ------
                            DETAIL: HIGH
                            EXIT

    Here are the options in more detail:


    LIVES: 3 / 5 / 7
    -------------------------------------------------------------
    This shows how many lives you will have from the start of the
    game.  (Never)

    
    GAME MODE: EASY / NORMAL
    -------------------------------------------------------------
    This tells you how the game will be played.  In EASY mode you
    will have less diamonds to  collect and you will only have to 
    hit the  baddies a few times    In NORMAL mode  then the game
    will  be  in default mode,  giving  you the  normal amount of
    diamonds  to collect  and  the baddies  will have  the normal 
    amount of hits.


    HISCORE: LOAD / SAVE
    -------------------------------------------------------------
    Selecting  between these  will not  do much as  they are, but
    pressing F10 while on this  option will let you save the high
    score table,  so you can  show off  your all time greatest to
    all your friends.


    LEVEL CODE: ------
    -------------------------------------------------------------
    The level codes help you jump  to a certain part of the game.
    Each level has  a code and to unlock  them you  need to get a
    pair of question  marks on the bonus round. The code  will be
    displayed when loading the next level,  jot it down and enter
    it next time round.  Todo this simply type the number via the
    keyboard.


    DETAILS: LOW / HIGH
    -------------------------------------------------------------
    The game has two detail levels. If you have a slow AMIGA such
    as a standard  A500 or A600 then use  the  LOW option, as the
    games runs faster, but you  don't have to. If you have a 1200
    or better then  use the HIGH  option  for all the  glory of a 
    overall  better display.  I have a 030 / 50Mhz AMIGA 1200 and
    the game runs without a single jump on the HIGH option.


@endnode
@node 8 "How to control the game"

        JOYSTICK
        --------

             LEFT - Move left
            RIGHT - Move Right
               UP - Move up
             DOWN - Move down
             FIRE - Throw your bouncy ball
        DOWN+FIRE - Pick up object while carrying nothing, and drop
                    object if carrying something.

        YOUR BOUNCY BALL: Once you have thrown your ball there are 3
                          ways to pick the thing back up,

                          1: Touch it
                          2: Press fire for 2 seconds.
                          3: Press the SPACE key.


        KEYS
        ----

        ESC     Kills you off, just incase you feel like it ?!

        P       Pauses the game, press again to resume.


        POWER-UPS
        ---------

        M, O, N, T, Y - Picking up any of these will be shown at the
                        bottom of the screen, collecting all will let
                        you skip the current level and play the bonus
                        round.

                BOOTS - Pick these up to go faster. The boots will
                        run out when you get hit or finish the level.

                STARS - Get this to be invincible for a few seconds.

             RED BALL - Make the ball faster.

        CROWNS, COINS - Collecting these will give you quite a handful
                        of points.


        OBJECTS
        -------

        SPINNING POLE - Get to here to complete the level.

              SPRINGS - Picking up these can help you to get to higher
                        levels.

                 KEYS - Colour-coded, use the right one for the right
                        door.

              BARRELS - Pick up and pile up to reach for higher places.
                        Also very handy for killing baddies more
                        quickly.

              BUTTONS - Jump on these to trigger something off, like
                        open doors and start platforms off.

        SPECIAL STARS - These are hidden well, there is one hidden in
                        each world.  To find them you have to explore
                        each level slowly and always try the
                        unordinary.

                        Collecting ALL four will unlock the cheats and
                        allow you to see the full ending.



    The Sub Game:
    --------------
    Collecting all of MONTYs name will bring up the bonus round, here
    you can collect extra lifes and level codes.  The level that you were
    just playing will automatically be completed.

    To play the syb game simply pick and match the cards. The bar on the
    right shows you what you have won and on the left shows you how
    much time is left todo so.

    To select a card move the highlighted box over the card you want and
    press FIRE.  Selecting any two the same will make you collect that 
    item.  What you have collected will be displayed on the left side of the
    screen.

    The level code will be shown on the next loading screen, jot the code
    down and enter it into the option screen to restart at that level.

    Guardians
    ---------
    Every 5 levels there will be a special baddie that is much bigger and 
    meaner than the rest.  They will need to be defected before you can 
    carry on with your quest to the next world.

@endnode
@node 10 "Other Eclipse/ASP games"

    Games Done
    ----------
    The following games I have also completed, they can be 
    downloaded from the ASP DESIGN homepage or the Aminet.

    @{"Survivors DX" system "ppshow GFX/3.Pak"}
    This is a gravity game, pickup all the men that have survived
    a deadly bomb attack. You will need a steady hand to guide
    yourself through each level. The new DX version has a special
    2 player version similar to Gravity Force/Power.

    @{"Super Tron" system "ppshow GFX/1.Pak"}
    Addictive 1/2 player game(Better in 2 player mode).  Guide to
    bikes around the screen, leaving a trail. The trail begins to
    make a maze, so now you have to watch you don't crash.

    @{"Mega Ball" system "ppshow GFX/2.Pak"}
    Guide a bouncing 'BOB' ball around mazes, using single joystick
    pushes.  Different puzzles such as invisible walls, painted
    walls, smaller gaps, and just plain hardness gets in your way.
    Very hard and game.

    Coming Soon
    -----------
    Conquest - Command & Conquer but for the amiga :)  I have
               plenty of new ideas but it is in early development.

    Here is what I have planned (So far):
    -------------------------------------
    · The game will run on any AGA Amiga with 8MB RAM (1.5MB Chip,
      6MB+ Fast) and a CD ROM.
      - Will help if you have a faster processor :)
    · 3/4 Selectable teams to play, each with their own pros and cons.
    · A pref program so that you can adjust Conquest to your machine,
      i.e.  Screen Mode, AHI, TCP/IP Stack, Memory, Processor etc..
    · Level editor for making your own levels.
    · Head to Head / Multiplayer levels.
    · CD Audio Tracks for 16-bit sound music.
    · A wide selection of destroy/seek/protect/deliver/commando missons.
    · Data Disks for expansion purposes.
      i.e. Extra missions, Different gfx, extra units/buildings.
    · Weather / Day+Night missions.
      i.e. The weather effects the units speed and sight as well as
           the dark.
    · Your ideas and comments.
    
@endnode

